DOC.brief_summary: Evaluation of glistenings in intraocular lenses implanted in normal patients following routine cataract surgery. The lenses used will be Model X-60 made by the AVS company Vs AcrySof MA50BM made by the Alcon company.
DOC.brief_title: Evaluation of Glistenings in Intraocular Lenses Implanted in Normal Patients Following Routine Cataract Extraction.
DOC.criteria: 18 years or older Bilateral cataracts requiring surgery Potential visual acuity of 20/40 or better in both eyes Require IOL power in range of 1525 diopters Pupillary dilation of at least 6mm Willing and able to provide informed consent and attend followup appointments to 3 years Any coexisting ocular disease or previous ocular surgery that would confound findings in the study, especially those effecting quality of vision. Examples include Macular degeneration amblyopia and prior epiretinal membrane peel.
